Definition: having or showing no mercy
Example: the merciless enemy; a merciless critic; gave him a merciless beating
Synonyms: noun, feeling, mercilessness, attribute, MERCIFUL, unmerciful, unmercifulness, BLOODY, HARD, INCLEMENT, IMPLACABLE, UNCOMPASSIONATE, UNKIND, having, or, showing, no, mercy, the, merciless, enemy, a, critic, gave, him, beating
Category: adj.all
